<div id="UG" class="well">

<p>Discover the rich history behind Iranian Jewish Life in Los Angeles from 1890-Present through this interactive site. Travel through time using the timeline, navigate across Los Angeles using the map of Iranian Jewish organizations in the region, and explore history through the story panel detailing historical events and community organizations' visions.</p>
<br>

<p class="bg-danger">To start, click on the History tab next to the User Guide tab to open the History panel. Then, simply scroll through the timeline or select a button to select a time period to view. Historical events and organizations formed during the selected timeline will be highlighted and populated both in the map below as well as the History panel you selected.</p>
<br>

<p>To learn more about a particular historical event or Iranian Jewish organization in Los Angeles, either click on an icon in the timeline or on the map, and the History panel to the right will highlight the details.</p>
<br>
<p class="bg-danger"><b>Tip:</b> Use the legend on the top of History panel to help you identify the types of organizations formed and the country or region with which a historical event is connected.</p>

<p>To view FAQs, click on the FAQ tab next to the History tab. You can click back to the User Guide tab or the History tab at any time.</p>
<br>
<p class="bg-danger">To learn more about the project, who we are, and keep up to date with the latest developments, please visit our website <a href="http://sandbox.idre.ucla.edu/dh150/groups/communitymovement/" target="_blank">here</a>
